title: 'Part of my soul': 4 takeaways from Biden's trip to Ireland
description: Like so many Americans do each year, President Joe Biden returned to Ireland this week in search of his roots, seeking some connection and some answers in the land his people left so many years ago.

title: Brazil's Supreme Court orders Bolsonaro to testify on January 8 riots
description: Brazil's Supreme Court has ordered Jair Bolsonaro to testify before Federal Police within the next 10 days, as part of an investigation into the events of January 8, when the former president's supporters attacked government buildings.

title: Russian court fines Wikipedia owner for article related to Ukraine invasion
description: A Moscow court has fined the Wikimedia Foundation for refusing to remove an article on Russian-language Wikipedia called "The Russian occupation of the Zaporizhzhia region," according to state media.

title: Opinion: When the Ukraine war finally ends, this is the battle we'll remember
description: When the war in Ukraine finally comes to an end, the besieged city of Bakhmut in eastern Ukraine will go down as one of the most recognizable symbols of the conflict.

title: Retail spending fell in March as consumers pull back
description: Spending at US retailers fell in March as consumers pulled back amid recessionary fears fueled by the banking crisis.

title: Markets digest bank earnings after recent turmoil
France braces for ruling on Macron's plan to raise retirement age
description: Heightened security is in place in the French capital Paris as the country braces for a crucial ruling on the constitutionality of divisive changes to France's pension system.

title: Analysis: World leaders are lining up to meet Xi Jinping. Should the US be worried?
description: Xi Jinping has had a busy couple of weeks.

title: On the 'rooftop of Japan,' a stunning 20-meter-deep snow corridor reopens to visitors
description: A giant snow corridor near the otherworldly Mount Tateyama, one of Japan's three sacred mountains, is reopening to travelers on April 15.

title: Analysis: Fox News is about to enter the true No Spin Zone
US 'disappointed' by Chinese court's decision to uphold death sentence for American citizen
description: The US State Department said Thursday it is "disappointed" by a Chinese court's decision to uphold the death sentence for American citizen Mark Swidan and called for his immediate release.

title: Iran executions up 75% as Tehran seeks to 'instill fear' in protesters, rights groups say
description: Iran executed at least 582 people last year, a 75% increase on the previous year, according to human rights groups who say the rise reflects an effort by Tehran to "instill fear" among anti-regime protesters.

title: Tibetan leader defends Dalai Lama after 'suck my tongue' request to boy
description: The head of the Tibetan government-in-exile has defended the Dalai Lama over a video in which the spiritual leader kisses a child on the lips and then asks him to "suck my tongue."
